{{Underlinked|date=January 2015}} '''Civil mobilization''' is the legal compulsion for civilians to work, in distinction to military [[mobilization]]. It has been used on a number of occasions by a number of governments. This generally makes [[General strike|striking]] illegal for the duration of the mobilization.
==Belgium 1964== To prevent a doctors strike the Belgium government, in April 1964, issued a civil mobilization order for hospital doctors and [[military doctors]].
